🇹🇭Interesting facts about Krabi

1. The name of the province in Thai means "sword" and has nothing to do with crabs;
2. On the territory of the region there is an outlandish beach "Shell Fossey", covered with slabs of pressed shells of ancient mollusks, the only beach in the province prohibited for swimming;
3. The province is famous for clothes made of Thai silk, pearl jewelry, pewter dishes, durian jam and orchids, which you can also try to take out as a souvenir;
4. At one of the dive spots of the province, when diving, you can see rare baleen cat sharks;
5. There is an amazing coconut ice cream here.

