🇵🇭

🔶Hundred Islands is a national park in the Philippines, where tourists can enjoy a lot of active entertainment. 

🔶Here you can go diving, kayaking, explore caves or fly on a zip-line. A beach holiday is also available to guests of the park. Interestingly, the islands are actually not 100, but 124.

🔶Tourists can only get to four islands that are specially equipped for receiving guests. 

These are:
• Governor's Island;
 • Children's;
 • * Caisson;
 • Marcos.

🔶Scientists believe that the islands were formed 2 million years ago. They were once part of an ancient coral reef that stretched far inland, but the decline in sea level led to the formation of islands.

